  <h1>The Life and Career of Max Verstappen</h1>
  <p>Max Verstappen is a <strong>four-time Formula 1 World Champion</strong> from the Netherlands and Belgium,
    racing for <em>Red Bull Racing</em>.</p>

  <h2>Early Life and Career</h2>
  <p>Max Verstappen was born on September 30, 1997, in Hasselt, Belgium, to a family deeply rooted in motorsport.
     His father, Jos Verstappen, was a former Formula 1 driver, while his mother, Sophie Kumpen, was a successful
     kart racer. Growing up in a racing-focused environment, Max began karting very young and quickly showed
     exceptional talent.</p>

  <h3>Max's Rise to Fame</h3>
  <p>After success in junior categories, Max debuted at age 17 with Toro Rosso in 2015, making him the
     <strong>youngest driver in F1 history</strong>. In 2016, he moved to Red Bull and won his first race
     immediately — becoming the youngest race winner ever. His fearless style made him a star overnight.</p>

  <h3>Most Famous Wins</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>2016 Spanish Grand Prix – Youngest winner in F1 history</li>
    <li>2019 Austrian Grand Prix – Comeback victory at Red Bull’s home race</li>
    <li>2020 70th Anniversary Grand Prix – Outsmarted Mercedes with strategy</li>
    <li>2021 Monaco Grand Prix – First Monaco victory</li>
    <li>2021 Dutch Grand Prix – First home win in front of orange crowd</li>
    <li>2021 Abu Dhabi Grand Prix – First World Championship</li>
    <li>2022 Belgian Grand Prix – Won from P14 showing domination</li>
    <li>2023 Dutch Grand Prix – Ninth straight win</li>
    <li>2024 Brazilian Grand Prix – Masterclass in mixed conditions</li>
  </ol>

  <h4>Media Backlash Surrounding Max’s Success</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Aggressive driving style</li>
    <li>Clashes with other drivers</li>
    <li>2021 Abu Dhabi GP controversy</li>
    <li>Bold media comments</li>
  </ul>

